documentation.author: Steve Wade
documentation.purpose:
This rule is designed to send an alert in PowerChart when a Discharge Patient order is placed and there are more than two antipsychotic orders (Non-PRN). The alert is intended to provide the order 'Reason for 2 or more antipsychotic meds'. If there is not an ordered or completed 'Reason for 2 or more antipsychotic meds' order this rule prevents the user from placing a 'Discharge Patient' order. The patient needs to have a Medical Service of DPUPSYCH or Psychiatric and been admitted >72 hours before the order is placed for the alert to be triggered. This rule will not trigger when an order is Cancel/Reorder unless there is another antipsychotic order for the same patient.
12/6/2016 Set OPT_LINK to L2 for templates L3, L4 and EKS_ORDERS_FIND_L templates.
documentation.explanation:
Evoke: ADDTOSCRATCHPAD Order List: consists of 24 antipsychotic meds (see below) Positions: User needs to be a Physician Relationship: Physician needs to have an Attending, Admitting or Covering relationship Encounter: Must be Medical Service DPUPSYCH or Psychiatric Encounter: Must be admitted > 4320 minute ago (72 hours) Action: When conditions are true, alert will display in PowerChart
24 Triggering Antipsychotic meds: Amitriptyline Aripiprazole Asenapine Brexpiprazole Cariprazine chlorpromazine clozapine fluphenazine haloperidol iloperidone loxapine lurasidone mesoridazine molindone OLANZapine Paliperidone Perphenazine Pimozide QUEtiapine Risperidone Thioridazine Thiothixene Trifluoperazine ziprasidone

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ORDER_E
templateDefinitions.definition: the triggering request contains an order ORD_METHOD OPT_ORDERS whose ordering physician OPT_QUALIFIER in OPT_ORDDOC

statements.statement: select if (par1 ="OTHER") from prsnl pl where pl.name_full_formatted != " " and pl.name_full_formatted not between "0*" and "Z*" and pl.active_ind = 1 and pl.physician_ind = 1 elseif (par1="ALL") from prsnl pl where pl.name_full_formatted != " " and pl.active_ind=1 and pl.physician_ind = 1 else from prsnl pl where pl.physician_ind = 1 and pl.active_ind=1 and cnvtupper(pl.name_full_formatted)=patstring(concat(substring(1,1,par1),"*")) endif pl.name_full_formatted, _hidden=pl.person_id order name_full_formatted

statements.statement: select distinct Form_Definition = if (t.seq = 1) dfr.definition else "*NONE" endif, _hidden = if (t.seq = 1) dfr.dcp_forms_ref_id else 0.0 endif, Description = if (t.seq = 1) dfr.description else "NONE" endif from dcp_forms_ref dfr, (dummyt t with seq=2) plan dfr where dfr.active_ind = 1 and textlen(trim(dfr.definition)) > 0 and textlen(trim(dfr.definition)) > 0 join t order Form_Definition

value.value: SELECT cv.display@NEWLINEFROM encntr_prsnl_reltn ep@NEWLINE , code_value cv@NEWLINEPLAN ep@NEWLINEwhere ep.encntr_id = trigger_encntrid@NEWLINEand ep.prsnl_person_id = reqinfo->updt_id@NEWLINEand ep.active_ind = 1@NEWLINEand ep.beg_effective_dt_tm < sysdate@NEWLINEand ep.end_effective_dt_tm > sysdate@NEWLINEand ep.expiration_ind = 0@NEWLINEJOIN cv @NEWLINEwhere cv.code_value = ep.encntr_prsnl_r_cd @NEWLINEand cv.display_key in ("ADMITTINGPHYSICIAN", "ATTENDINGPHYSICIAN", "COVERINGPHYSICIAN")@NEWLINEdetail@NEWLINElog_misc1 = "FOUND", @NEWLINElog_message = build2("prsnl = reqinfo->updt_id: ", reqinfo->updt_id, " - reltn (", trim(cv.display,3), ") = ", log_misc1)@NEWLINEgo@NEWLINE
